Letter was sent from White Star Lines to brother of officer James Moody who died on board the Titanic in 1912 . 
  It asks for £20 to have his body returned to his home in Scarborough - almost £2,000 in today's money . 
  Mr Moody was on watch when the ship hit an iceberg and died in the disaster . 
  Company bosses say family will have to pay for his burial and transport . 
  He was the sixth junior officer to die after the ship sank . 
 